American journalist Jill Carroll, working for the Christian Science Monitor, was kidnapped in Iraq.
Her Iraqi interpreter was killed during the abduction.
The Monitor pleaded for her release, emphasizing her dedication to revealing the truth about the Iraq war.
Carroll's family issued an emotional appeal for mercy, highlighting her love for Iraq and its people.
The US government denied negotiating with insurgents in Iraq.
Carroll's captors threatened her with execution unless female prisoners were freed.
The situation remains tense as efforts continue to secure her safe return home.
